TI  - Pedagogy Wheel for Artificial Intelligence: adaptation of Carrington's Wheel
AU  - Jiménez-García, Eva
AU  - Martínez, Natalia Orenes
AU  - López-Fraile, Luis Antonio
T2  - Revista Iberoamericana de Educación a Distancia
AB  - La integraci&oacute;n efectiva de la Inteligencia Artificial (IA) en la educaci&oacute;n es necesaria para aprovechar sus beneficios en el proceso de ense&ntilde;anza-aprendizaje. Este art&iacute;culo propone la adaptaci&oacute;n de la Rueda de la Pedagog&iacute;a de Carrington a una Rueda de la Pedagog&iacute;a para la IA, con el fin de ofrecer un marco pedag&oacute;gico para integrar la IA en la educaci&oacute;n. La metodolog&iacute;a de investigaci&oacute;n utilizada se basa en una revisi&oacute;n y mapeo sistem&aacute;tico junto a un estudio bibliom&eacute;trico del an&aacute;lisis de co-ocurrencia de t&eacute;rminos para identificar los clusters tem&aacute;ticos relevantes que respalden cient&iacute;ficamente la necesidad de la adaptaci&oacute;n de la Rueda. La nueva rueda atiende a los cuatro clusters obtenidos (Integraci&oacute;n de la IA para mejorar la educaci&oacute;n, Uso de tecnolog&iacute;as educativa en el proceso de ense&ntilde;anza y aprendizaje, Dise&ntilde;o e innovaci&oacute;n pedag&oacute;gica y Educaci&oacute;n Sostenible y &Eacute;tica) y presenta anillos conc&eacute;ntricos que explican c&oacute;mo incorporar gradualmente la IA en diferentes niveles cognitivos (Taxonom&iacute;a de Bloom) e integraci&oacute;n tecnol&oacute;gica (Modelo SAMR) ambos adaptados a la IA, con ejemplos de herramientas y aplicaciones. Adem&aacute;s, se incluye un nivel Reflexivo-Metacognitivo que aborda la &eacute;tica y responsabilidad en el uso de la IA. En conclusi&oacute;n, la rueda adaptada a la IA es una opci&oacute;n viable para mejorar la eficacia y eficiencia de la educaci&oacute;n, con la condici&oacute;n de que los docentes participen en la planificaci&oacute;n y ejecuci&oacute;n del proceso de ense&ntilde;anza y aprendizaje para garantizar su &eacute;xito. Cabe mencionar la importancia de mantener la rueda actualizada debido a la aparici&oacute;n constante de nuevas aplicaciones.Resumen alternativo:The effective integration of Artificial Intelligence (AI) in education is necessary to harness its benefits in the teaching and learning process. This article proposes the adaptation of Carrington's Pedagogy Wheel into an AI Pedagogy Wheel, aiming to provide a pedagogical framework for integrating AI in education. The research methodology employed is based on a systematic review and mapping, coupled with a bibliometric study of term co-occurrence analysis, to identify relevant thematic clusters that scientifically support the need for the adaptation of the Wheel. The new wheel addresses the four obtained clusters (Integration of AI to enhance education, Use of educational technologies in the teaching and learning process, Pedagogical design and innovation, and Sustainable and Ethical Education) and presents concentric rings that explain how to gradually incorporate AI across different cognitive levels (Bloom's Taxonomy) and technological integration (SAMR Model), both adapted for AI. The wheel includes examples of tools and applications to illustrate the implementation. Furthermore, a Reflective-Metacognitive level is included that addresses ethics and responsibility in the use of AI. In conclusion, the wheel adapted to AI is a viable option to enhance the effectiveness and efficiency of education, provided that educators engage in the planning and execution of the teaching and learning process to ensure its success. It is worth mentioning the importance of keeping the wheel updated due to the constant emergence of new applications.
